Title: Marley & Me - The Puppy Years

reviewText: This is definitely a kid-oriented movie and on that level, it succeeds as a cute enjoyable film.  Adults might find it too contrived and difficult to appreciate.THE PUPPY YEARS is obviously an attempt to cash in on its successful origins but is so amateurishly done, there is no real comparison.  First problem is the decision to have the animals talk.  It's become a tired device and the voice characterizations aren't particularly effective.  The human actors tend to overact and poor Donnelly Rhodes (DaVinci's Inquest) is forced to act as second banana to the dogs.But I'm being too Scroogish...family films are intended to entertain families looking for wholesome entertainment.  This movie should meet that criteria just fine.
Title: Marley & Me - The Puppy Years

reviewText: This is a nice PG family film. Anything with dogs that is done well is good entertainment.  Nice to watch with our Grandchildren.

reviewText: What can I say?  YUCK!  Not nearly as cute and funny as the first Marley & Me.  Save your money, don't even bother renting it!  I usually LOVE dog movies, but this was not at all what I expected.
